text:
Is there an operator for checking if a value in array `does not contain`  rather than containing?
*Example:* 
_blog tags_ [business, technology, isFeatured]
Then on the Blog Listing when I call `content in contents` I can remove any `isFeatured` posts that have those tags?
Is this what youre asking for?
Ya, I didn't realize there was a `is not containing` operator. Thanks!

Haha for sure! So there really isnâ€™t an operator for it in hubl but you can combine the expression tests to check for it.

`is containing`  is one expression and then you can throw the `not`  in there to negate it. There are actually a bunch of pretty slick expression tests that are worth taking a peek at in the docs here

<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/operators-and-expression-tests>
